snippet.textDisplay:
I genuinely fear for Everton.

2020 summer: Ancelotti struggles to attract the names he wants to bring to the club
2021 After a mid-table 11th place finish, Ancelotti quits, sparking a boardroom rift and revealing huge debts.

2022 After not being seen at the ground in nearly four months, rumours start that Moshiri plans to sell
2023 With spiralling debts, a boardroom rift and still no sign of the stadium, a Chinese consortium are rumoured to be buying Everton
2023 Duncan Ferguson is fired with Everton deep in a relegation battle
2024 Wayne Rooney can't keep Everton in the top flight
2024 Stadium plans finally shelved due to relegation, Moshiri selling up, crippling debts and lack of clarity from the new Chinese owners
2025 Everton's promotion bid falters in the play-offs. Rooney leaves to take charge of Premier League Derby County citing a lack of direction at Everton
2026 Everton finish in the lower half of the Championship for only the second time in history
2027 Lack of investment and crippling debts see the club relegated to League One for the first time in history.

2028 Everton's first League visit to Prenton Park ends in a 3-1 defeat.
2029 Average attendance at Goodison Park is 13,000. The new American owner announces that Everton will leave Goodison for a new ground in Warrington in 2032. Part of the plan cites that Everton need a geographic area of their own to build a fan base as Liverpool is effectively described as a 'one club city'
2033 Warrington Everton win the Championship in their new 32,000 capacity stadium.

We were absolutely terrible.
And just don’t have any young players like that who are ready to jump in.

Siggy and Schniderlaine were woeful.
No fight in them whatsoever.
Wandering around pointing. Wondering what is going on.
Coleman is finished. So is Delph.

Fair play to Liverpool.
They played us off the park with quality and hunger we just didn’t have.
So fair play.
